    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="815"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d815">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Dr. <persName type="from">Lobo</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Venezuela</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Dr. David Lobo, chargé d’affaires <hi rend="italic">ad interim</hi> of Venezuela,
                    presents his compliments to the Secretary of State, and in compliance with the
                    request expressed by the Secretary at the interview of October 24 has the honor
                    to inclose herewith a brief review of the boundary question pending between
                    Venezuela and Great Britain.</p>
                <p>He asks the Secretary also to inform him on what day it will be convenient to the
                    former to have him call at the Department for a fresh discussion of the subject
                    referred to.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
